text.tspan: HoneyBadger allows a network of N nodes with at most F faulty ones, where 3 f < N, to input contributions and to agree on a sequence of batches of
contributions. The protocol proceeds in epochs and outputs one batch in each epoch. It never terminates: It handles a continuous stream of incoming contributions
and keeps producing new batches from them. All correct nodes will output the same batch for each epoch. Each validator proposes one contribution per epoch,
and every batch will contain the contributions of at least N - F validators.
